-- Kenya Tea Workers Ordered to End Strike, Resume Talks Over Plucking Tools
-- B y   C o n s o l a t a h   L u c a s
-- 2010-11-01T16:33:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/kenya-tea-workers-ordered-to-end-strike-resume-talks-over-plucking-tools.html
Kenya’s Industrial Court ordered that
workers in the country’s tea industry end a strike and to resume
talks over the use of tea-plucking machines by Nov. 12, a labor
union said.  The Kenya Plantation and Agricultural Workers’ Union will
tomorrow advise its members to go back to work, Issa Wafula,
assistant secretary general of the union, said in a phone
interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Consolatah Lucas in Mombasa at 
